ACT 1 — LEAVING NEW-RHODE
Purpose of Act 1

Act 1 should feel like a straight manhunt.

The audience belief:

Alistair is a violent fanatic who tried to murder Liliane and fled west.

The working theory:

He is dangerous, unstable, reckless, and not covering his tracks.

Only beneath that surface do we quietly build:

Garvin knows more than he says;
Garvin is subtly controlling pace;
Marion distrusts him;
Tanya observes details others miss;
the western route is stranger than expected.

No one suggests Alistair wants pursuit.

That remains hidden.

The act ends at the Boiling Sea.

SCENE 1 — WESTERN LOGISTICS GATE — DAWN

Cold sulfur morning.

The western blast gates of New-Rhode grind open.

Acid runoff trickles through sealed channels beneath heavy steel decking.

Fine metallic dust skates across the concrete in little silver streams.

Beyond the gate:

grey plains, broken ridges, pale stone, and endless metallic desert.

The convoy waits.

Katie.
Sally.
Lilly.
Abby.

Big pressure wheels. Tall fiberglass masks. Reflective foil solar canopies folded down over their backs.

Beside them sits Barnabus.

Older. Heavier. Scarred. Improvised armor plating welded over half its frame. The ugly duckling.

Marion slides out from underneath Barnabus holding a wrench between her teeth.

Cass/Kess arrives with Tanya and security crates.

Garvin leans against Katie smoking, looking west.

Not at them.

At the desert.

Cass immediately dislikes him.

CASS
Garvin?

GARVIN
Depends who's asking.

CASS
Chief Admin Cass BravoSierra.

GARVIN
Then yes. Bad luck for both of us.

Cass ignores the jab.

Tanya kneels near the western exit road.

Dust has preserved Alistair's boot prints surprisingly well.

She photographs them.

TANYA
Stride is even.

She checks spacing.

TANYA (CONT'D)
Long stride. Confident pace. No limp. No hesitation.

CASS
He put a round through the governor and walked out like he was late for dinner.

TANYA
Didn't avoid cameras either.

MARION
Or patrol drones.

Everyone glances over.

Marion wipes grease from her hands.

MARION (CONT'D)
Three drone towers cover the west corridor. Blind spots are tiny. He crossed clean through them.

Cass folds his arms.

CASS
Some killers like spectacle.

TANYA looks up.

CASS (CONT'D)
Attention. Infamy. Admiration. The thrill of being chased.

MARION
Admiration?

CASS
You'd be surprised what madness wants.

Tanya studies the footprints again.

TANYA
Or he's careless.

GARVIN
Careless men die quick out west.

CASS
Then hopefully he dies tired.

Garvin crouches beside the tracks.

Touches the dust.

Feels wind direction.

Then stands.

GARVIN
Move now and we keep trail.

CASS
Then move.

Garvin doesn't move.

GARVIN
One thing first.

He points at the convoy.

GARVIN (CONT'D)
Outside the wall, those become your world. Batteries, wheels, suspension, weather. If one dies, your plans die with it.

MARION
Listen carefully. That's frontier poetry. Means don't break my machines.

Small smile from Tanya.

No smile from Cass.

Garvin crushes his cigarette.

GARVIN
Mount up.

The convoy rolls west.

New-Rhode slowly disappears behind them.

SCENE 2 — INTO THE DUST DESERT

The land opens wide.

Cold thin air.

Pale grey rock.

Metallic dust plains.

Harsh light.

Wind scraping grit across stone.

The mules lumber over uneven terrain, rocking violently.

Inside Katie:

Cass rides with Garvin.

Inside Barnabus:

Tanya rides with Marion.

INSIDE KATIE

Cass studies navigation data.

A straight line west.

No doubling back.

No broken path.

No obvious attempt to conceal direction.

CASS
No effort to hide trail.

GARVIN
Maybe he panicked.

CASS
Tracks are too steady for panic.

GARVIN
Then maybe he's arrogant.

CASS
Or mad.

GARVIN
Same thing often enough.

Cass watches him.

CASS
You always this cheerful?

GARVIN
Only when armed men drag me into deserts.

Cass almost smiles.

Almost.

GARVIN (CONT'D)
Storm coming tonight or tomorrow.

CASS
How do you know?

GARVIN
Sky's wrong.

CASS
That scientific?

GARVIN
Kept me alive.

INSIDE BARNABUS

Barnabus hums like a buried reactor.

Old analog needles twitch beside digital screens.

Tanya watches fascinated.

TANYA
This mule shouldn't exist.

MARION
Engineers Guild agrees.

TANYA
Why keep it running?

MARION
Because Barnabus is immortal and spiteful.

Tanya smirks.

Then serious again.

TANYA
Garvin checked the convoy before we arrived.

MARION
Saw that.

TANYA
Normal?

MARION
For him? Maybe.

TANYA
You trust him?

Marion thinks.

MARION
I trust him in bad weather.

TANYA
And otherwise?

MARION
I trust him less than bad weather.

That lands.

SCENE 3 — THE FIRST MARKER

Midday.

The convoy halts at a ridge.

Tanya found something wedged beneath a stone.

A folded strip of reflective foil.

Clean.

Deliberate.

Too deliberate to be litter.

Marion turns it in her hand.

MARION
Fresh.

TANYA
No oxidation.

CASS
Marker?

GARVIN
Could be scrap.

MARION
No chance.

Garvin shrugs.

GARVIN
Then someone dropped scrap neatly.

Tanya flips it.

Three tiny puncture holes in one corner.

Patterned.

CASS
Code?

GARVIN
Could mean anything.

MARION watches Garvin carefully.

Too quick an answer.

TANYA
You've seen them before.

GARVIN
Seen lots of junk.

He walks back toward Katie.

Marion quietly to Tanya:

MARION
He's lying.

TANYA
About what?

MARION
Not sure yet.

SCENE 4 — AFTERNOON PUSH

Travel montage.

The convoy pushes harder west.

Visuals:

giant metallic dunes;
acid-scarred rocks;
silver dust clouds;
sunlight glittering across mineral plains;
Barnabus towing Abby briefly over rough ground;
Garvin repeatedly checking the horizon;
Tanya sketching the puncture pattern;
Cass replaying assassination footage.

Over CB:

MARION
Sally's suspension is whining again.

GARVIN
Ease throttle over ridges.

CASS
We're losing speed.

GARVIN
You're losing impatience. Different thing.

Later—

TANYA
Garvin.

GARVIN
Yeah.

TANYA
Those punctures. Mean anything?

Beat.

GARVIN
Nope.

Too quick.

Marion hears it.

Her suspicion deepens.

SCENE 5 — BOILING SEA RIDGE — SUNSET

The convoy crests a ridge.

Everyone goes quiet.

Below stretches the Boiling Sea.

A shallow steaming basin stretching impossibly wide.

Yellow crust.

Warm vapor.

Heat shimmer.

And descending footprints.

Alistair went straight into it.

Garvin slams Katie to a stop.

GARVIN
Stop. Everybody stop.

Convoy brakes hard.

Cass climbs out.

CASS
Tracks continue.

GARVIN
Yeah.

CASS
Then we continue.

GARVIN
No.

CASS
Why?

GARVIN points down.

GARVIN
Natural fission basin under the crust. Hot ground. Radiation pockets. Bad footing. Ugly death.

MARION
Pretty though.

GARVIN
You have problems.

MARION
Many.

Tanya studies the tracks.

TANYA
Still straight.

CASS
No hesitation.

MARION
No wandering either.

Garvin says nothing.

Cass looks west.

Steam rising.

Unknown beyond.

CASS
Can we cross?

GARVIN
Not safely.

CASS
Can he?

GARVIN
Maybe.

CASS
How?

GARVIN
Luck. Madness. Or he's tougher than he looks.

Tanya quietly:

TANYA
Or he knew where to step.

Garvin glances at her.

Tiny reaction.

Nearly invisible.

Marion catches it.

Important beat.

Wind blows hot vapor upward around them.

Cold sky overhead.

Boiling earth below.

Cass turns back to the group.

CASS
Camp here. We move at first light.

Garvin looks west.

Troubled.

Quietly:

GARVIN
West gets worse.

Cass hears him.

CASS
Good.

Beat.

CASS (CONT'D)
I hope he's miserable.

Camera pulls wide:

small convoy at ridge edge, steam rolling upward, vast dead desert ahead.

END OF ACT 1.
